The paper deals with speech recognition using both audio and visual modalities, which falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of recurrent neural networks (RNN) and connectionist temporal classification (CTC) loss function suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of temporal alignment, which could fall under signal processing (cs.SD).
